The Duchess is located opposite of the W Hotel and housed in the old KAS Bank Building it is beautifully done! Service is a little American, with the 'Hi, my name is Peter and I am your host for tonight', but it is prompt, friendly and spot on!  The food not only tickles your tastebuds, several dishes have some form of spectacular table preparation. If you are a chocolate fan: try the chocolate explosion. And if you don't want to be wheeled out at the end of your dinner: share it! We think The Duchess is gonna be a beloved, young acting, golden oldie in Amsterdam. ——————————————————————— Food ⭐️⭐️️⭐️⭐️ Service ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️ Ambiance ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️ ——————————————————————— #restaurant #lunch #dinner #theduchess #kasbank #whotels #spuistraat #amsterdam  #amsterdamrestaurants #amsterdamfood #food #proefwerk #foodstagram

Day 3 - Amsterdam - Sillmacka: (un)traditional Swedish herring salad. Garlic herring, rye & knackebrod and strawberry butter. Amazing modern introduction if you're a little nervous to try pickled herring for the first time. The herring is so delicate in texture and has a mild but distinct flavor. This place has also been awarded Best Concept Coffee in Amsterdam, so a must for coffee lovers. Highly recommend visiting this joint if you're ever in town! #Amsterdam #Netherlands #herring #foodadventures #wanderlust #foodie #seafood #salad #sillmacka #scandanvian #day3 #eurotrip #travel #whattoeatinamsterdam #amsterdamfood

Day 4 - Amsterdam. Saw a line forming in front of this tiny little store and decide to tag along. Best decision! This perfectly white half dome was a combination fresh dense cream and the creamiest ice cream I've ever had. If you've ever indulged in whipped cream straight from the can, this is right down your alley. The store only sells this in one flavor but also has other little pastries available. #amsterdam #eurotrip #day4 #icecream #cream #amsterdamfood #europe #wanderlust #foodie #travel #foodadventures #sosimple

Amsterdam appears to be the capital of street food and we are taking full advantage! There's even amazing Vegetarian food to be had all over the place and a perfect example is this Vegetarian Hot Dog. A superb herb sausage with all the essential toppings. It even makes the meaty hot dog (that was actually delicious) look nowhere near as interesting. Take that.  Dear Sydney, our Vego is never coming back. Apologies, TGOF  In all seriousness though, this city has truly amazing food that offers something for everyone. Definitely add it to your to-do list if you are looking for more than the seedy "cafes" found in the overpriced Red Light District. #TGOFeatoutEurope

🎶 Take me on a Magic carpet ride..... 🎶 Today's box was a culinary journey inspired by a recent trip to Morocco & the desert 🌴  A quarter aubergine, slow roasted 'til nice and crispy, then painted with a fresh garlic, lemon & tahini sauce, garnished with chopped mint & sesame seeds | chickpeas marinated with a blend of Moroccan spices, cinnamon heavy, with thinly sliced raw red onion | brown rice laced with parsley, citrus, dill, fresh orange segments, black olives & toasted almonds | A whole roasted & peeled Romano pepper curled up with cashew, date, lemon verbena & basil pesto | pickled red onion & perfectly cubed carrot & butternut salad with chilli & wild cumin dressing | spicy mung bean pate with lots of lemon & the holy trinity -chilli, garlic & ginger.... All garnished with pomegtanate rubies & rose petals... Pheeew that's a tummy full o' happiness 😉  How did you enjoy your #Cropbox today? This one is Turkish food from the central part of Turkey originated in Konya and one of my favourite. Etli Ekmek or "bread with meat" has very thinner and crispy base and topping is not spicy mostly based on thinly chopped green pepper,tomato and minced meat. My favourite is "kusbasili" which means thinly chopped lamb fillet instead of minced meat. Havzan is a small,clean restaurant offering very friendly service. Soups are also nice. Just give it a try! #amsterdam #pastaconsardeamsterdam #amsterdamfood

When I was away on my trip I always made it a habit to have food at cafes and not inside overwhelming fancy restaurants. Reason being that restaurants that serve all kinds of cuisines generally never have quality food 🙄 (unless you are dining at a really really costly one). Cafes on the other hand never disappoint and fit ones budget. Italian cafes serve awesome italian food, spanish cafes serve awesome spanish food and so on. 🤘  I fell in love with pizzas all over again 😄 Don't want to sound harsh but I really don't like the kind of pizzas chains like Dominos and Pizza Hut sell here.  Italian cafes on the other hand served awesome italian food all round let alone pizzas. I fell in love with Tuna fish toppings 😁 I miss the food I had all through the trip 😞  Nice memories! 😊  #streetsofamsterdam #amsterdam #amsterdamfood #italiancafe #pizzalovers #pizzaislovepizzaislife #europe #eurotrip2015

De Pijp, an Amsterdam neighborhood found just south of the canal ring, translates into English as 'The Pipe’ - an early reference to either the public prostitution or the shape of the neighborhood. Historians disagree.  For the last couple of years, an actual pipe, the Amsterdam metro, has been digging its way under De Pijp. Not surprisingly, building a subway in a city that's below sea level is kind of tricky and led to the misfortune which was the 'Great Heineken Debacle of 2014,' when the Heineken brewery fell into a giant sinkhole. Even without its top tourist destination and the constant fear of sudden, gaping pits, De Pijp has managed to evolve into a neighborhood that lifestyle bloggers describe as “trendy” and “alive.” On sunny afternoons, try Sarphatipark if you're inclined to pop the top and get some color. The Albert Cuyp Market (#albertcuypmarkt) is (supposedly) the “largest daytime market in Europe” and has a few interesting food stands, but you're better off heading to Pho 91 (@pho91amsterdam), Spaghetteria (@spaghetteria_pastabar), or The Butcher (@thebutcheramsterdam). (**TIP - There’s also great Surinamese just off the market on Eerste van der Helststraat.) For shopping, there’s Charlie + Mary (@charlieplusmary), All The Luck In The World… (@alltheluckintheworld), and several other boutiques on the same block of Gerard Doustraat. If you're working away from the office, Stadskantine has plenty of window seating and a good atmosphere. For coffee, Scandinavian Embassy (@scandinavianembassy) and CT Coffee & Coconuts (@coffeecoconuts) are good spots.  Find more suggestions for the best of De Pijp on Sightseen's Neighbourhood Collections.  Download #sightseenapp from the App Store. #tbt to the best poffertjes in Amsterdam. These little Dutch babies are fluffy, sweet and perfect to pop in your mouth. They come with an assortment of different toppings (Nutella, jams, butter etc) but they were recommended to be eaten with butter and powered sugar. The best I've had are in Nieuwmarkt Square from a food stand. A must eat every time I'm in Amsterdam.

Ahhh...a sunny Sunday in Amsterdam. Does it get any better? Boats on the canals, packed terraces, biking through the park. Lekker weertje!  On the way to @boccacoffee today, we passed a wobbly tourist completely off his tits with chunks of vomit dripping from his beard. Not bad for noon on a Sunday. (“Goed zo, meneer! Enjoy your flight back to Luton!”) A few minutes later, we were delivered this display of civility pictured above. The card you can't read because of the overwhelming amount of filters applied to this poorly shot image describes the tea at hand. Apparently, it's “blossomed, dewy, and bouquet.” If you've ever walked into @boccacoffee and wondered - “How is it possible for this huge, beautiful space to exist in the Centrum? I mean, there's only like 12 seats. How do they make any money?”, it's because @boccacoffee is an anomaly that should be celebrated. Rumor has it that the shop on Kerkstraat is a flagship and not-so-top-secret training facility for Bocca Coffee operatives. Basically, we get to enjoy spacious, high-ceilinged, “blossomed, dewy, and bouquet” Sundays while Bocca takes a hit on the lavish space in the name of bettering the brand overall. Fair trade!* (*Bad coffee joke.) Check out @boccacoffee and find all the best coffee places in Amsterdam for your sunny Sundays with the Sightseen App.  Download #sightseenapp from the App Store. This is Back to Black (@backtoblackcoffee), a great little cafe near the Rijksmuseum.  Whereas in most cities the terms are interchangeable, in Amsterdam, there's definitely a distinction between a “coffee shop” & a “cafe.” The importance of this distinction depends entirely on your mood, sense of adventure, & probationary status.  All Amsterdamers have stories of visitors naively announcing - “Where are these weed shops? Let's toke some green!” Nobody sounds cool saying “toke some green,” & it’s in these situations when Amsterdamers are forced to flip the big kill-switch known as “Project De-escalation: Keep Uncle Steve Away From The Weed.” Step 1 involves a long bike ride followed by trips to brewery/tasting rooms like Borouwer'ij (@brouwerijtij) or Butcher's Tears. If you can sneak in a few rounds of bitterballen with the heavy beers, it’s likely your charge will forget their boastful weed promises.  If Step 1 doesn’t work, Step 2 suggests a visit to a mellow coffee shop & slyly ordering - “Mag ik je zwakste weed? I have an idiot tourist who doesn't need anything stronger than hash cut with a ton of rolling tobacco.” Once in hand, take your visitor on a walk to smoke & see the city. They’ll last 30-45 minutes before crashing back at the hotel/AirBnb/your extra bedroom. Easy peasy!  The worst situation is when the visitor stays energetic through the bike ride, dubbels, bitterballen, & your kind offer to order weed. If they say “It's cool, dude. I’ve smoked a lot of weed, I know the score,” the only option is traditional Dutch directness. “No, Uncle Steve, you don't know the score. In fact, the score has been hydroponically mutated to such levels that you're going to end up wobbling down Leidsestraat wearing a knit Amsterdam beanie and asking strangers for the ‘Hanses Blinkers Hotel.’ I don't want to be on a cold bench listening to you repeatedly slur 'I might puke,' while my actual friends have normal evenings. But, hey, you get to go back to Rochester or Atlanta or Fort Worth & tell everyone about the time you were ‘in Amsterdam looking for coffee and ended up at a coffee shop.’” Find the best coffee & coziest cafes in Amsterdam on Sightseen.

Cantinetta is owned by the Dutch/American couple Claudia and Deborah. The latter is showing off her cooking talent and Italian roots in the kitchen, while Claudia is serving the dishes in the Roman inspired osteria. They prepare their own pastas during the day, which make up the most of the menu. The wine list changes very frequently as well as part of the menu. Fortunately the side dish of the non pasta main stays the same: mashed potato (with pancetta! 😋) and endive.  Grab a quick bite here and ask for a tasteful bottle of wine and go home happy! ——————————————————————— Food ⭐️⭐️️⭐️⭐️ Service ⭐️⭐️⭐️ Ambiance ⭐️⭐️⭐️ ——————————————————————— #restaurant #dinner #osteria #Cantinetta #cantinetta.nl #declerqstraat #amsterdam #wine #pasta #roman #italianfood #italianwine #italian #ossobuco #mashedpotato #pancetta #endive #amsterdam  #amsterdamrestaurants #amsterdamfood #food #proefwerk #foodstagram

Madam is the panorama bar and restaurant on the 20th floor of the newly developed @adam_toren. It is the square part, just beneath the observation desk (HELLO IM ADAM) and above the 19th floor revolving restaurant where they will serve 5- and 8-course dinners. Madam has a more brasserie style menu with classics like steak tartar, Caesar salad and rack of lamb.  Going up in a spectacular elevator and welcomed with a glass of Champagne, we were first overtaken by the VIEW! Words can't describe it properly, but maybe you can stay tuned on @amsterdamview and see for yourself.  Our sneak peak 4 course dinner started with smoked salmon followed by tom kha kai, supreme chicken and yes: there was still some room for a chocolate mousse. We loved it. Service and food are only in need of some fine tuning, but all is done from the heart.  We are curious what Moon is going to be like! But Madam had a terrific first try out evening! ——————————————————————— Food ⭐️⭐️️⭐️⭐️ Service ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️ Ambiance ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️ ——————————————————————— #restaurant #club #cocktails #lookout #brasserie #Madam #MadamAmsterdam.nl #AdamToren #AdamToren.nl #IJoever #amsterdamnoord #amsterdam #wine #amsterdamrestaurants #amsterdamfood #food #proefwerk #foodstagram  #adamtoren #adamlookout #preopening #sneakpeak #tryoutdinner

"Geef mij maar Amsterdam, dat is mooier dan Parijs" - Johnny Jordaan  The Jordaan - traditional home of the dramatic vibrato that is Jordaanlied music and current home of Amsterdam's “most beautiful canal," De Brouwersgracht. A wobbly grid of quiet, narrow streets, the Jordaan is as much Amsterdam heritage as wooden shoes & rain.  On Rozengracht, along the bottom edge of the Jordaan, you'll find Salmuera (@sal_amsterdam) w/ an exceptional mix of cocktails & ceviche. Further down, the terrace at Brandstof (@barbrandstof) is the perfect place to observe one of the great spectacles of Amsterdam – the convergence of pedestrian, bike, scooter, car, taxi, bus, & tram. Who will win?? (SPOILER – It's usually the tram.) Heading north off Rozengracht leads into the Jordaan & over some of the city's prettiest canals. If you get nice light & want to win Instagram, Egelantiersgracht (#egelantiersgracht) & Bloemgracht (#bloemgracht) are great options.  Saturday mornings on Westerstraat, you can either have beers & cigarettes with the locals at De Blaffende Vis (#blaffendevis) or head to the organic market at the Noorderkerk (#noorderkerkmarket). If looking for dinner, De Reiger (#dereiger) has maybe the best ribs in Amsterdam & definitely the coolest restaurant cat. Daalder (#daalder), in a former jazz bar on Lindengracht, also has great food, but unconfirmed if there’s a restaurant cat.  After dinner (or anytime really), the Jordaan has a solid supply of brown bars. Cafe Thijsen (@cafe_thijssen) & De Tuin (#cafedetuin) are usually fun. But if you're looking for a truly “cultural” experience, the fluorescent pink, late-night beacon of Cafe Nol (@cafenolamsterdam) will definitely blow up anything you have to do the next morning.  For more Jordaan suggestions, check out the Sightseen app.  Download #sightseenapp from the App Store. The neighbourfood cafe Bar Mick is in the middle of the upcoming Spaarndammerstraat. It opens at 9 for coffee and breakfast and serves different menus throughout the day. The dinner menu only has meat and vegetarian options. We ordered the bavette and veggie burger, but the waiter mentioned that the vegetarian burger was actually not that good and advised us the vegetarian ravioli. So we did.  The bavette was cut with the grain, so not as tender as this 20,50 € costing larded piece of meat should be. The ravioli was well undercooked. Add up the waiter that folds up the laundry in the bar during service, literally reads up the daily specials from the chalk board behind us and we come to the conclusion that there are far better ways to spend your euros. We go for better! ——————————————————————— Food ⭐️ Service ⭐️ Ambiance ⭐️⭐️ ——————————————————————— #bar #cafe #restaurant #barmick #barmick.nl #spaarndammerstraat #westerpark #spaarndammerbuurt #amsterdam #amsterdamrestaurants #amsterdamfood #food #proefwerk #foodstagram

Saravanaa Bhavan is the new positive surprise in Indian vegetarian delight. Imagine a purple lid ceiling, the ugliest chesterfield chairs available and staff that doesn't know exactly what it serves. But hey, they are friendly. But then add the extensive menu with loads and loads of deliciously prepared dishes and the 75% Indian people that are visiting this restaurant. And when they are here in these big numbers, you know it is good. And they are helpful! Because you next table neighbors know what you should order. Because we couldn't choose, we ordered the Saravanaa Special with all kind of small tries, white rice and papadum. And it was great! Reservations are advised.  This is a go people! ——————————————————————— Food ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️ Service ⭐️⭐️ Ambiance ⭐️ ——————————————————————— #indianfood #restaurant #saravanaabhavan #saravanaabhavan.nl #stadhouderskade #vanwoustraat #depijp #amsterdam #dosa #amsterdamrestaurants #amsterdamfood #food #proefwerk #foodstagram

Loetje Centraal has touched down last year in the wooden coffee house opposite of Amsterdam Central Station.  It all started long ago in the Pijp with the small and cosy Cafe Loetje. Their secret is a commonly known fact by now: They bake the very tender meat in plain Blue Band. The "Loetje Group" now has 9 restaurants including their latest addition in Gorssel of all places. The Little Princess became a Disneyland. But what do we learn from Disneyland? They offer quality, staff is well trained and the ambiance fine. And we all love a bit of  that sometimes. But still it feels like "Honey, they blew up Cafe Loetje". ——————————————————————— Food ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️ Service ⭐️⭐️⭐️ Ambiance ⭐️⭐️⭐️ ——————————————————————— #lunch # diner #restaurant #loetje #loetje.com #centralstation #stationsplein #depijp #amsterdam #amsterdamrestaurants #amsterdamfood #food #proefwerk #foodstagram

The Breakfast Club has opened a new branch on the Haarlemmerplein, which is still underdeveloped in terms of bars, restaurants and especially terraces. Where the first Breakfast Club is known for serving breakfast all day, here you can also enjoy dinner. Breakfast and lunch during the weekend are packed here. We went for a salad of the new dinner menu and it was very quiet. Portion wise we were not fully satisfied, but the price and taste was right. We got a nice salad with cray fish, loads of those little guys actually. It could have had a serving of bread and a little more green salad. And a price adjustment from now 10 to let's say 12 euros would be fine for dinner! Service was ok. Friendly, helpful, but they were struggling a little bit with the new menu. We will come back for another salad or the famous breakfast pancakes. ——————————————————————— Food ⭐️⭐️⭐️ Service ⭐️⭐️⭐️ Ambiance ⭐️⭐️⭐️ ——————————————————————— #breakfast #lunch # dinner #drinks #cocktails #restaurant #thebreakfastclub #thebreakfastclub.nl #haarlemmerplein #westerpark #amsterdamwest #salad #crayfish #pancakes #amsterdam #amsterdamrestaurants #amsterdamfood #food #proefwerk #foodstagram

Vondelpark/3's biggest feature is definitely its large sunny terrace overlooking the park. It has recently celebrated its first year anniversary and is here to stay. Service is a mix of hospitality minded people and students running drinks and dishes. The food is good in taste and presentation. The fresh tuna on the Niçoise salad was served medium rare. Perfect! However we like our egg on the Caesar poached, and think that the choice for a cooked one is merely based on the number of dishes that need to be prepared then on the connoisseurs' taste. They do a very nice family breakfast where your table is loaded with tasty items. ——————————————————————— Food ⭐️⭐️⭐️ Service ⭐️⭐️⭐️ Ambiance ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️ ——————————————————————— #breakfast #lunch # dinner #drinks #terrace #restaurant #vondelpark/3 #vondelpark3.nl #vondelpark #filmmuseum #vondelcs #vanbaerle  #vondelkerk #amsterdamzuid #ceasar #nicoise #amsterdam #amsterdamrestaurants #amsterdamfood #food #proefwerk #foodstagram

📸👉@mariskabuiter  Does it seem like there's a food fest every weekend in Amsterdam? Well, there is. And sometimes more than one at the same time.  This weekend is Butcher's Heaven, which as you can infer from the name is all about creative vegetarian options and plant-based supplements. There will be no dead animals and fire pits. Just free yoga workshops and matcha tea. Be sure to stop by the Freedom Flush stand for a chance to get 15% off their 30-day juice cleanse program.  At the #centralemarkthal in the West. Open today and tomorrow until 23:00.  Download #sightseenapp from the App Store. Wat weet jij over pistache (ijs)? De pistache noten uit ons ijs komen uit Bronte, dat ligt aan de voet van de Etna in Sicilië. Sicilië is de enige plek op aarde waar pistachenoten worden geteeld. De oogst is één keer in de twee jaar, zodat de boom haar kracht kan behouden. De minerale zouten in de vulkanische aarde zorgen voor een unieke zilte nasmaak. De smaak van ijs laat zich niet anders beschrijven dan echt pistache! #vansoest #utrechtsestraat #chocolade #chocolate #iamsterdam #amsterdamcityguide #lostinamsterdam #amsterdamworld #amsterdamcity #amsterdamtrip #amsterdamshots #amsterdamfood #amsterdamlife #atamsterdam #pistache #pistacheijs #icecream #icecreamamsterdam

Worst Winecafé is a little tucked away in the Barentszstraat near the Haarlemmersquare. They serve fine small dishes for yourself or to share. Their great wine selection is served with passion and know-how. We love it, but it is rare in Amsterdam... We started of with some bread (baked daily at Restaurant As), anchovies with broad beans and pecorino and a clean green salad with mustard dressing. A good start! Tasty and pure.  From the sausage (worst) department we ordered fennel sausage served with braised pepper and fennel and the chicken sausage which came with morels and creamy spinach. We loved the former, liked the latter.  The cosy atmosphere and relaxed setting is perfect for a after work evening or laid back weekend night. Bike into the Zeeheldenbuurt and check it out! ——————————————————————— Food ⭐️⭐️️⭐️⭐️ Service ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️ Ambiance ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️ ——————————————————————— Worst Wijncafé Barentszstraat 171 020-6256167 www.deworst.nl Open: Tue-Sat 12.00-0.00, Sun 10.00-22.00 ——————————————————————— #restaurant #dinner #lunch #wine #winecafé #Worst #zeeheldenbuurt #haarlemmerplein #amsterdam #amsterdamrestaurants #amsterdamfood #food #proefwerk #instafood #foodstagram #restaurantreview #sausage #fennel ——————————————————————— Follow AMSTERDAM RESTAURANTS for more reviews of your next to know favorites.

We finally made it to the girls and guys of Pluk, a fine addition to the healthy lunchrooms in Amsterdam. They have done a great job interior wise and sell loads of bring home items.  When you enter, the male to female ratio drops dramatically. But that's nothing to worry about. What you do need to worry about is the danger of ordering the entire menu. The freshly prepared food and drinks are great here! They tickle your tastebuds and pleasure the eyes.  Service wise: we love table service, but the plukkers chose differently. Fair. All in all we are more then ok with that. The Dutch have handed down the chairmanship of the EU to the Slovakians, which means that the former Marine Land of the Dutch Navy is ours again! Reason for us to explore this extraordinary piece of land adjacent to the Scheepvaartmuseum with its replica of the VOC tall ship 'Amsterdam' at which a beautiful view is granted. The terrace is one of its most pleasant surprises. As is the beer menu. From fresh to the more dark beers, all with a special twist. The combination makes for a great evening on the waterside. That was our first evening. We went back for lunch in the bar. And that was good too. Service was friendly though sometimes a little slow. The sandwiches are tasty and the juices refreshing. And they know how to make a good espresso. Drop by when you are in the hood! We continued to the Scheepskameel. Stay tuned for our review! ——————————————————————— Food ⭐️⭐️️⭐️ Service ⭐️⭐️⭐️ Ambiance ⭐️⭐️⭐️ ——————————————————————— Brewery Homeland Kattenburgerstraat 5 020-7232550 www.pensionhomeland.com  Open: Mon-Sun 7.00-0.00 ——————————————————————— #breakfast #lunch #dinner #juices #coffee #sandwiches #marineterrein #marine #amsterdam #amsterdamrestaurants #amsterdamfood #food #proefwerk #instafood #foodstagram #restaurantreview #hamoflamb #tomatochutney ——————————————————————— Follow AMSTERDAM RESTAURANTS for more reviews of your next to know favorites. Aight, so there's this dude who owns a small Japanese restaurant on the top floor of an Asian grocery. It's a one man show. He takes your order and you can see him cook and prepare food right there in front of you. He moves frantically when there are be several people waiting (and that's often the case), but don't worry about the wait for your ramen or pancakes. Take a seat. He will serve you your dish. I went on a Sunday and wanted to go again the next day to try another dish. However, he doesn't work on Mondays and Tuesdays. I was saddened by this fact so I decided that I wanted to tip him because the ramen was delishhh. But he humbly wouldn't accept my tip. Sir, you are an awesome chef. The place is kind of a secret but I'm sure more and more people will find it and it won't be such a secret anymore. Also, his restaurant is only open, at the most, 5 hours each day. I hope to come visit you again and try those pancakes.  #takajapanesekitchen #Amsterdam #amsterdamfood #netherlands #ramen #japanesecuisine #food #foodie #foodporn #yum

text: First a short history lesson: Escoffier is seen as the greatest innovator of French cuisine and having learned everything from him, Henri Thijs returned to the Netherlands to open a deli-restaurant combination together with entrepreneur Dikker. This combination was new to the Netherlands and was an instant hit. The succes story is larded with multiple branches, prices, a Michelin star, and the opening of an hotel. Back to here and now. We passed by for lunch and had two of the classic salads. The Niçoise salad came with a severe piece of freshly grilled tuna and other fine ingredients including a poached (we love it poached) egg. The tuna had some natural tough membrane, which made us fillet the fillet. But hey, that happens. We found ingredients of the same quality in our Caesar salad with chicken. Classic and perfectly served. Bread came after we asked for some pieces. The restaurant is styled in a modern and warm way, leaving room for the old brick wall and other original details. ——— Food ⭐️⭐️️⭐️⭐️ Service ⭐️⭐️⭐️ Ambiance ⭐️⭐️⭐️ ——— Thijs by Dikker & Thijs Prinsengracht 438 (near Leidsestraat) 020-6250150, reservations possible www.thijsbydikkerenthijs.nl Open: Sun-Thu 10.00-0.00, Fri-Sat 10.00-1.00 ——— #coffee #lunch #dinner #drinks #prinsengracht #leidsestraat #escoffier #hautecuisine #amsterdamcentre #amsterdamrestaurants #amsterdamfood #food #proefwerk #instafood #foodstagram #restaurantreview #amsterdamreview ——— Follow AMSTERDAM RESTAURANTS for more reviews of your next to know favorites.  Tag the friend that you want to bring here.

Mimi Latteria Milanese is located on the long long Kerkstraat near the corner with the Nieuwe Spiegelstraat. It is inspired on the small grocery stores that popped up in the post-war 50’s in Milan selling farmers products and serving home cooked dishes. This inspiration is to be found in the menu solely, because in the ambiance you would expect an ‘artisan’ touch but it is very contemporary. The restaurant is Italian owned and staffed, something we appreciate and gives a little confidence in taste. The menu provides a cross-section of Italian cuisine. Bruschette, some soups, pastas, and classic mains like vitello tonnato, coteletta alla Milanese, some salads and last but not least dolce like Tiramisù and dark chocolate pie. We chose for the Millefoglie, made of bread, vegetable and tomato caponata and mozzarella. Now technically what was on our plate was mozzarella, but after smoking it for about 15 minutes, the taste becomes much more dominant and then it is called scamorza. Not something we particularly appreciate and where other dishes were on the menu with scamorza specifically named, this dish hadn’t. So we asked for some mozzarella instead and were told that this was actually mozzarella, but then smoked. After a short discussion about clear communication and some waiting for the new dish, we got what we wanted. And it was more then tasty the way it was advertised. Heya, the secret sauce speaking,  Hanging at Sir Hummus for a while, I overheard so much gossip about me. Some people assume I’m made of avocado or tahini. Others are convinced I’m liquid Wasabi.  Everybody tries to crack the secret that makes me awesome, but here’s the honest truth: I just don't know. I am bit like superman. No clue what I’m made of or where I came from. Only thing I know is that I’m VEGAN. And I’m allergic to Kryptonite.  It makes me happy to know a Sir Hummus plate isn’t complete without me! 🤗

Around the corner from Sichuan Kitchen (one of Sightseen’s favorites) and light-years from the @cannibaleroyale locations in Spui and De Pijp. The RLD version stands oddly on a street of terrible tourist pizza and waffles for stoned hostelists. But maybe when you can't get a table at the Spui location (and you're feeling particularly patient), it's worth firing up the bike bell and navigating the zombie hordes for some ribs in the RLD. Heute Morgen waren wir (wie jeden Morgen) im Bagels&Beans frühstücken. Es ist eine Amsterdamer Café-Kette, die sehr stark auf Nachhaltigkeit und Natürlichkeit setzt. Alles wird super frisch zubereitet und schmeckt wahnsinnig lecker. Man kann aus acht verschiedenen Bagels wählen - es gibt sogar einen weizen- und einen glutenfreien. Zum Frühstück gab es heuten den Oathie-Bagel mit Hummus, Hühnchen, Salat und Mango-Chutney 😋 Jetzt sind wir mit fast einer Stunde Verspätung auf dem Weg gen Heimat. Happy Weekend! Ahhhh... the life of a freelancer. Uncrowded yoga classes at 11am. Endless hours practicing craft and perusing "actionable insights on productivity." Flippantly dangling your (un)availability to recruiters. But if you're a freelancer not in one of those fancy coworking spaces for entrepreneurs, independently-wealthy, and/or startups, chances are you've hunkered in a cafe, milked a single munt thee for two hours, and sucked the wifi dry. Where to go to keep the baristas from discovering your ruse?  We made a 'Where To Work' collection on Sightseen featuring the most comfortable, work-friendly, inspiring, and inviting cafes in Amsterdam. Visiting from NYC and need a picture of the latest Fantastic Man for your Instagram? Try @cloudamsterdam . Looking for a nice window view to finish your thesis? Maybe #destadskantine in De Pijp? In town from Seoul and want to post a dispatch on 'Northern European Street Style Memes' (whatever that means)? What about @fridaynextamsterdam on Overtoom?  Work! Drink coffee! Tell social media about it! Download #Sightseenapp from the App Store. I proudly announce the winner of my #bestveggieburgerofamsterdam competition! My absolute favorite vegetarian burger in Amsterdam is (drumroll please).... the Dutch Weed Burger! 🏆  There are so many reasons to like it that I don't know where to start. The patty is one of the few ones that I tried that didn't fell apart. The bun is rich in taste and crispy. The Dutch Weed Burger is fully plant based, so suitable for vegans and great news for our planet. It's also kosher, halal and quite healthy as it contains seaweed and chlorella. And one of the best things about it? It's available at many places throughout the Netherlands, and sometimes even abroad (it'll be in London on October 22nd). I hope that my list inspires you and I'd love to hear your thoughts if you tried one of the veggie burgers on my list!

AMSTERDAM • So many types of flavoured sausage - some with vegetables mixed in, others with bier! Noodermarkt is a small, local but popular market selling an array of organic products such as bread, pasta, cheese, seafood and vegetables. There's also a flea market next door.

AMSTERDAM • There are macaroons, and then there are kokosmakronen - coconut macaroons! We tried some amazing ones found at Noodermarkt.  From @thedutchtable: Dutch have an incredible cookie culture. Grocery stores stock shelves of the most amazing combinations, shapes, ingredients and flavors. Coconut macaroons, or kokosmakronen, are found in a variety of shapes and sizes. Some are small and high, others piped in a circle and flat. Some are yellow (depending on whether you include the egg yolk), others plain white, but the flavor and texture is always moist, coconutty and sweet. Kokosmakronen are usually baked on circles of edible potato starch paper.
AMSTERDAM • The bread and flavoured dips at Noodermarkt - so many options to choose from.
AMSTERDAM • Hotchpotch is the real Dutch “stamppot ” of mashed potatoes with vegetables served with a sausage of butcher Louman, a meatball & bacon €17.
AMSTERDAM • Home made apple pie with ice cream €6.50 from Moeders. So good!

AMSTERDAM • Cycled to Amsterdam Bos (Forest) on Sunday morning then had (more) delicious pancakes at the end of our ride. From the top: Apple with powdered sugar and cinnamon €6.80; ham pineapple and cheese with Mediterranean spices €9.40; pineapple with powdered sugar, roasted almonds and whipped cream €9.30; and hot cherries and chocolate with powdered sugar €9.80. The forest is beautiful - definitely worth a morning cycle there!

Here we go, heading back to Europe! This time to London and Amsterdam! I have never been to London, so I am excited!! I actually disagreed with my boss about the necessity of this trip, despite wanting to go for personal reasons, but I'm going.👏🏻 So,  figured I had to add another new city to visit. For just $100 round-trip, I'm heading to Amsterdam a day after I get to London, then I'll head back to London to work and explore. . Amsterdam is known for many things, pancakes are one of them, so thought this was  fitting Bitmoji for a foodie😋 Looking forward to visiting Anne Frank's house and Van Gogh's Museum, as well as strolling along the canals. . In London, I'm hoping to visit Harrod's and its famous food hall, see Big Ben, Buckingham Palace, London Bridge, eat some fish & chips, sticky toffee pudding, spotted dick and I a bunch of other stuff👏🏻😋 #ChowChick
locationName: LAX International Airport, Los Angeles, California

To cool off from the jalapenno🌶I made The zucchini mango salad🙏🏻. ———————————————— INGREDIENTS: 1 zucchini  1 mango  10 cherry tomatoes  2 tbsp rice vinegar 1 tbsp roasted sesame seed A pinch of pepper A pinch of salt. ———————————————— INSTRUCTIONS 1. Make the zucchine small in the spiralizer.  2. Cut the mango in small slices.  3. Roast the sesame seed in a pan.  4. Cut the cherry tomatoes in four.  5. Blend everything with the rice vinegar in a bowl and at some pepper and salt. Enjoy!  #amsterdamfood #amsterdam #veganamsterdam #food #salad #mangosalad #spiralizer #healthyfood #friendscooking #photooftheday

The fondue at Café Bern is typically shared by 2 – 4 people, so they serve a big basket of bread (about 2 full baguettes, divided into 4 pieces, and pre-cut for smaller bites). - I had the weirdest encounter!  I was dining at the bar and a couple was next to me with my bread basket sort of between this woman and me.  We had exchanged a few words, pleasantries, then I began to eat. Next thing she says to me (as she is taking some of MY bread), “I’m going to eat some of your food.” I don’t know that I said anything, but my face said more than enough because she immediately apologized and wouldn’t stop apologizing.  Incredibly presumptuous and weird! 😱 😜Not that I couldn’t share, but it was so shocking that she would just help herself and announce, not ask if she could. They were getting their own food, so not sure what that was about, but I was in Amsterdam, so maybe she had smoked a lil too much herb 😂😂 Here’s the lovely fondue I ate. #ChowChick 🍞🍞🧀🍞🧀🍞🧀🍞🍞

text: While exploring in Amsterdam, of course I got hungry (well, when am I not hungry?) for a little snack, I popped into Simon Meyssen again.  This time I had to try the Appelrondo. Yummy in my tummy!  A nice little apple cake snack! #ChowChick

I had many recommendations for pancakes in Amsterdam, but since I was near this one on my list, I had to pop in. Here I am about to indulge in a variety of pancakes at The Pancake Bakery (it’s near the Anne Frank House, so went there right after). #ChowChick

I felt like I needed to make up for not getting to many food spots, so ordered a few different pancake plates at The Pancake Bakery in Amsterdam. I started with these very traditional  Poffertjes with butter and sugar. My server said this is very Dutch!  Yum!#ChowChick

Next on my pancake pig-out at The Pancake Bakery in Amsterdam was another traditional Dutch one on the savory side. My server was kind enough to recommend I do the children’s version (can you imagine it any bigger?!) This had Gouda cheese and bacon (the bacon was on the underside of the pancake), which is on my fork, and my server insisted I eat it with A LOT of syrup, so I obeyed! 😱🐷 #ChowChick

OMG, last post for a lil bit, cuz I'm making myself hungry!!😂😂 I saw the Autumn Special (pancake with cinnamon ice cream, poached pears, cranberry compote, Belgian chocolate flakes and whipped cream) on the menu at The Pancake Bakery in Amsterdam and couldn’t pass that up, so that finished off my visit there!  Look how thin that pancake is!  I really didn’t have room in my belly for much at this point, but loved the pears and the ice cream! #ChowChick

There's a burger under that egg! Amsterdam had THE BEST food and I'm a picky eater (getting better). I was walking to another place and passed this restaurant on my way and came back another day. I was sick coming from Iceland and had a wicked sore throat my first couple of days in Amsterdam. I got this delicious and huge burger with equally delicious and fresh fries. Every thing was seasoned and so so good. They had a tea which soothed my throat almost instantaneously as well with lemon ginger and honey. I left stuffed and took home a slice of chocolate pie which was also amazing. The decor of this place was super cute and service was great. Blank canvas... Meringue is always so pretty when it's perfectly white and fluffly! I prefer italian meringue over french meringue for my lemon pies, because I "cook" the eggwhites when incorporating the boiling hot sugar syrup making it more sticky and gooey than the lighter french version. Also italian meringue stays intact for much longer, whereas french meringue becomes runny again quite quickly and doesn't stay good for long. This blank canvas is just dying to get caressed by the flames of a blowtorch and turn into caramelised brown meringue!!!

📒🖋 Op zaterdag 4 maart zal er in Creative Haus een schrijfcursus worden georganiseerd door Nelleke Lamme-den Boer!  Voor meer informatie  verwijzen we jullie door naar onze Facebook pagina!  Maar hier alvast  wat meer informatie over Nelleke zelf:  Nelleke Lamme-den Boer is docent Creatief schrijven. Vanuit haar bedrijf Tekstkwartier organiseert zij cursussen en workshop in en buiten Amsterdam. Zij schrijft poëzie en korte verhalen. Ze is een ongebundelde dichter en treedt regelmatig op om haar werk te kunnen voordragen. Schrijven is voor haar een manier van vormgeven, een rustgevend creatief proces.  Zien we jullie op 4 maart? "Twaalf jaar geleden kwam onze droom uit om in het hartje van Amsterdam mensen kennis te laten maken met onze eigen recepten en eten. We verbouwen zelf al vele jaren onze eigen groentes en kunnen je zodoende precies vertellen wat er op je bord ligt. Er worden geen bestrijdingsmiddelen en andere onvriendelijke methodes gebruikt om jou van een heerlijke lunch of high tea te voorzien, alles is puur en eerlijk! Op veler verzoek hebben we onze recepten samen gebundeld en kun je nu ook ons kookboek kopen. Wel op tijd bij zijn, want dat loopt harder dan we ooit hadden durven hopen...!" #amsterdam #denhaag #rotterdam #utrecht #leiden ##haarlem #nijmegen #leeuwarden #groningen #hightea #recepten #lunch #interview #amstelveen #zoetermeer #theetijd #biologisch #eerlijketen #organicfood #mooiemensen #amsterdamcity #amsterdamfood #amsterdamhotspot

Soooooo together with @Andazams and @bluespoonamsterdam i'm hosting a little meet up on Feb 11th. Where we'll start very very early as we'll be shooting Sunrise to start the day. (Keep in mind....sunrise is e-a-r-l-y 😴) As there are very very limit places we have to work with invites. But... five of those invites could go to you guys/girls! If you have seen my stories, their breakfast is A-MA-ZING, and yes you'll have to wake up early but there will be coffee. Lots of it. And breakfast. (Who doesn't love food right?) ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ So, if you want to be considered for an invite make sure to let me know below if you want to come! And why we should chose you over the other willing people.  I wish I could have everyone who wants to join come along with us but unfortunately, in that case there's not enough food for me 🤷🏼‍♂️🙈😂😂 ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ Doubting the food is worth it? Ask @fannetiek, as we went to pre-taste this morning. (And she'll be there again on the 11th) Oh there's also something with the Prinsengracht suite as well. And trust me on this, that suite is pretty nice! ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ Ok. Let us know!

Turns out there is no "BEST #RAMEN PLACE IN #AMSTERDAM", it really depends on what you're after! We think the best find for deeply flavoured #vegetarianramen is at #ChefTakasKitchen tucked away on the 2nd floor of #TokoDunYong in Europe's oldest #Chinatown. It takes some serious skill to get so much flavour just from veg! That said, our pick for the best #tonkotsuramen is still the newish (and  relatively unknown) @sappororamensora in De Pijp.  #bestveggieramen #instafood  #amsterdamlunchspots #nieuwmarkt #amsterdamguide #soup #liquidlunch #wheretoeatinamsterdam #dubbellekker #iamsterdam #hiddenamsterdam #veggiefood #vegetarianamsterdam #veggingout #amsterdamrestaurants #yolkporn #bestvegetarianfoodinamsterdam #vegetarianfood #amsterdamfood

After a loooong 2 weeks of working 13 days in a row, crazy hours (one day I worked from 7:30 till 22:00 😨), and poor food choices, I think I deserved a Saturday night eating out 🙏 I'm not really familiar with the vegan food scene in Amsterdam after being away for so long, so we decided to try out @meatless_district 💪 Lovely, luxury wee place with gorgeous food options and the best staff ❤ Good to have a vegan restaurant option for romantic night outs or fancy  birthday parties 👌 . . We just finished the most incredible meal at @restaurantdekas in Amsterdam. The restaurant is connected to a greenhouse, where they source many of the vegetables used in their dishes. 🍅🌶🌽🍎 The menus are fixed, but the chef can accommodate dietary restrictions, which was great for people like us who can't eat everything. So I don't normally post after photos of meals but I had to share this massive meal I was served in Amsterdam. Lamb Chops to start (top) look like 6 which is a huge portion compared to US restaurants but turns out 2 were double ribs. 8 Chops!! Holy Moly was I full. That all for 26.50€ which is the States would be like $50 for 3 Chops. Perfectly cooked medium rare and the stamppot part was potatoes, cabbage and spinach mixed. All with a beautiful port reduction I ate the hell out of.  @restauranthaesjeclaes #amsterdamfood #haesjeclaes @findmeglutenfree #findmeglutenfree #findmeglutenfreeapp

Ormai è un rito andare a trovare l'amico @sandervanmelick ... la ricchezza dei suoi piatti riesce a spingermi sempre sino ai campi... al mare... alle stalle... assapori la freschezza... e la sua territorialità.  Amo la sua concentrazione mentre pensa a te, invitato della serata. Pensa a come amerai sorprenderti masticando lentamente sapori profumi... nei piatti di Sander trovi l'Olanda un  Olanda reale. Ma anche la capacita di incastonate la croccantezza  di altri paesi come l'Italia con il suo letto di cavolo nero a sua maestà il cervo... grazie, un grazie dal profondo del cuore amico Sander... P.S. Have you guys tried Mojo? It's a delicious Cuban marinade made with lashings of sour orange juice, plenty of cumin, garlic and oregano. If you don't have access to sour oranges, then no problem, use normal fresh orange's and lime juice, to achieve that tart taste. There are many variations of the recipe as there are with many recipes. You can use it on seafood, meats, it's usually used a lot with pork or chicken. Here I've used it on red snapper. If you like garlic and the tart flavours, this one is for you. Recipe on the website soon, go to www.nyamfoodie.com  By the way I'm hosting a pop up at Scrapyard Cafe on Wednesday 8th March. If the pictures on this feed make your mouth water, why don't you come and try some of my food for yourself. Dining starts at 6.30pm, if you'd like to book your spot email your reservation to wearenyam@gmail.com  Come nYam and jam!  #foodography #foodnetwork #foodpic #foodporn #foodism #foodlover #foodstagram #moderncaribbean #moderncaribbeanfood #moderncaribbeanflavors #moderncaribbeancuisine #yummy #foodinspo #amsterdam #amsterdamfood #amsterdamcity #f52gramsfoodpic #f52grams @cafescrapyard #like4like #follow4follow

30 min wait in line for Best Thai in town. 👌  THAI BIRD RESTAURANT  An elegant restaurant with more than 100 seats, Thai Bird serves tasty dishes to a crowd of hungry diners nightly. Although the restaurant is large, there seems to be a line out the door most evenings. The wait is never very long however, and soon you will be seated with a Singha in hand (did you know it is pronounced “Sing” and not “Sing-ha”?). Begin your meal by sharing an order of loempia or saté, tom yum soup, or perhaps Northern Thai lobster meatballs. The menu has something for everyone, with seafood, chicken, noodle, beef and vegetarian dishes. Most main courses run from €15-18 each and come with steamed rice. Service is quick and friendly.  #amsterdamfood #amsterdam #thai #redcurry #instafood #delicious

// Pancakes Amsterdam 🥞 // 🗺 Prinsengracht 277, 1016 GW Amsterdam, Pays-Bas ✍🏻 Coralie 3/5 // Moi : 3,5/5 🇫🇷 Avec @coralie_jeanne nous avons passé 3 jours à Amsterdam pour son anniversaire, voici donc un petit interlude néerlandais avec des pancakes 😋 Coralie : C'était bon mais pas surprenant. Les serveuses étaient adorables mais le lieu grand et blanc fait assez aseptisé, ça détonne un peu pour moi, je mets un 3/5. Moi : Le pancake néerlandais ressemble en fait à une grosse crêpe, ou une "pescajoun" de mon enfance, spécialité du quercy, c'était bon, parfait pour le petit déjeuner et le service était vraiment très agréable, les gens à amsterdam sont des anges ! Je mets un bémol sur le fait que leurs toilettes soient payants 50c, un restaurant, pour moi, se doit d'offrir l'accès à des sanitaires gratuitement ! Nous avons pris le pancake salé le plus cher et à 12,5€ cela reste très correct. 🇬🇧 Coralie : Waitresses are very nice but the place is big and white, not very warm. The food is good but not amazing.  Moi : Netherlands pancakes look like the "pescajoun", a thick crepe from my county, memory of my childhood, it was good. One bad point for the place is that you have to pay 50c to go to the toilet and I think every restaurant should let you access the toilet for free. We took the most expensive pancake and it was 12,5€ so quite correct.  #pancakes

One of the most famous Grand Cafes in Amsterdam. I stumbled upon this place on our hunt for good food. The cozy interior with the beautiful art decor details made it feel like I just walked out of Dutch beauty right into modern Parisian romance. The salad beef carpaccio was definitely one of the best I've ever had served with a blend of pine nuts, Parmesan and pesto, and for someone who is always on the hunt for a good carpaccio, this definitely exceeded my expectations. With truffle in abundance, I couldn't resist a meal here! Definitely a tick on the list for all the things my tummy loves!  For those who DM'd me about my previous food post about price points, this was comparatively  affordable taking into consideration the quality of service, food & ambience.  #theragtradeeats #theragtradetravels . . . . . . . #foodie #food #foodgasm #eatingfortheinsta #foodbloggers #lifestyle #travel #amsterdamfood #truffle #foodporn #travelblogger

The plan was to go Salsa Shop. People had been raving about it for some time. One look at the food though and Mr.G and I were both standing outside with a sad face. Through the pouring rain we ran all the way to Wagamama. To spice things up, and feel like I was trying out something new anyhow, I was brave and decided to try out a new dish. Usually, I go for Yasai Itame or Chicken Kare Lomen, but this time I took Chicken Raisukaree–and wasn't disappointed at all. Wagamama delivers, baby! What you see on the plate is chicken stir-fried in a coconut and lime curry sauce with mangetout, peppers, red and spring onions served on sticky white rice and garnished with red chillies, coriander and lime. I am also in love with the space, and actually, I like this whole street nowadays. The restaurants are mainstream but they are all pretty pimped up. Great for a super easy dinner with friends before taking the party elsewhere. #dontbeasnob #spiceitup #ilike #chicken #raisukaree #asianfood #food #wagamama #amstelstraat #rembrandtplein #amsterdam #amsterdamdinner #amsterdameats #amsterdamfood

Indonesia was a former Dutch colony & has left its mark in the Netherlands with its cuisine. There are many Indonesian restaurants in Amsterdam & we decided to try one just to see how authentic the food is. MAX was recommended by our hotel & we tried the Rijsttafel (Indonesian banquet). Many small Indonesian dishes are served together with rice for sharing. I'd say the dishes are somewhat authentic, though adapted to suit the locals' taste. For example, the curry dishes weren't spicy at all (at least not to the Indonesian standard) & the achar had cauliflowers & capsicum. #Rijsttafel #indonesianfood #foodinmymouth #foodphotography #ilovesharingfood #foodporn #foodforfoodies #foodspotting #fooddiary #sharefood #food #instafood #foodgasm #burpple #amsterdamfood #travel #travelphotography #wanderlust #traveling #travelgram #holiday #vacation #instatravel #amsterdam

《荷蘭 · Keukenhof》 Fresh StroopWaffle (€2.50) @Keukenhof Tulip Garden  會食上癮嘅窩夫。 基本上荷蘭周圍都有得買包裝版，但新鮮整嘅就比較少見。新鮮窩夫比一般嘅大塊同稔身，新鮮出爐所以會更重牛油香味，加埋溶溶地嘅糖漿起中間，真係食到停唔到口。 Tips: Amsterdam市中心都有間叫Stroopwaffle Heaven食新鮮窩夫。  Waffles that cause you addicted. Basically you'll find packed stroopwaffles everywhere in the Netherlands, but fresh ones are less commonly seen. Fresh waffles are relatively larger and softer than usual ones, and they taste much more buttery since they're freshly baked, together with the half melted syrup in between, you just can't stop craving for it. Tips: There's a store in Amsterdam city centre called Stroopwaffle Heaven which also sells fresh stroopwaffles. 地點/ Location: Keukenhof Tulip Garden  @myfoodyssey #food #foodstagram #foodie #foodporn #yummy #hkig #foodig #waffle #nom #igershk #igersnetherlands #amsterdamfood #hkfoodie #travel #igersuk
